underline;text-decoration-style:inherit;text-decoration-thickness:inherit;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"http://52.175.20.166/careers/current-vacancies#\">请参阅英文版</a></p>'),(363,'Senior / Design Engineer','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Responsibilities</strong></span></p><ul><li><p style=\"text-align:center;\">Monitor site progress and coordination works</p></li><li><p style=\"text-align:center;\">Prepare method statements or technical submissions</p></li><li><p style=\"text-align:center;\">Manage and interface with internal and external stakeholders to uphold construction safety and quality standards</p></li><li><p style=\"text-align:center;\">Work in close collaboration with Site supervisory staff</p></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p><ul><li>Degree holder in Civil Engineering&nbsp;or related disciplines</li><li>Minimum 4-7 years\' practical experience in civil projects</li><li>Committed to the achievement of the highest standards in all construction activities including safety and quality assurance</li><li>Proven team leadership and contractual awareness</li><li>Good communication skills</li><li>Candidates with less experience will be considered&nbsp;as Site Engineer</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:#838182;\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr.p@buildking.hk\" target=\"_parent\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">bkhr.p@buildking.hk</span></a><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">or clicking&nbsp; </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;color:#0000ff;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\"><span style=\"color:#0000ff;\">Apply Online</span></a></p>'),(364,'Environmental Engineer / Assistant Environmental Engineer','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Responsibilities</strong></span></p><ul><li>Prepare, implement and update the Environmental Management Plan</li><li>Responsible for routine site inspections and internal and external audits</li><li>Monitor and improve environmental performance of the Project</li><li>Provide technical support to ensure the Project complies with legal and contractual requirements</li><li>Coordinate with site staff, subcontractors and client\'s representative for day-to-day activities</li><li>Perform ad-hoc tasks as assigned</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p><ul><li>Degree holder / HD in Environmental Engineering&nbsp;or related disciplines</li><li>2 years’ experience in contractor company</li><li>Completed the Environmental Officer Course&nbsp;is preferable</li><li>BEAM Pro qualification and relevant BEAM Plus new building FA experience is preferred</li><li>Good command of spoken &amp; written English and Chinese</li><li>Immediate available is highly preferred</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp; <a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr@buildking.hk\">bk<span style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\">hr.p@buildking.hk</span></a>&nbsp;or clicking&nbsp; <a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;color:#0000ff;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\">Apply Online</a></p>'),(365,'Senior Project Quantity Surveyor','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Responsibilities</strong></span></p><ul><li>Prepare and monitor project budgets and costing</li><li>Measure and value sub-contracts and assist in agreement of sub-contract interim / final accounts</li><li>Review documentations and identify value variations, subcontract payments and preparation of sub-contract liabilities</li><li>Conduct cost analysis, budgeting control, measurement and collation of records at our construction sites</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p><ul><li>Degree in Quantity Surveying or related disciplines</li><li>At least 10 years\' relevant experience</li><li>Experience in re-measurement, valuing variations, cost control, contract administration, claims preparation and dealing with sub-contractors\' accounts</li><li>MRICS or HKIS professional qualification will be added advantage</li><li>Strong negotiation and communication skills</li><li>Fluent English and excellent writing skills</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr.p@buildking.hk\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">bkhr.p@buildking.hk</span></a><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">&nbsp;or clicking&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">Apply Online</span></a></p>'),(366,'Quantity Surveyor - Civil','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Responsibilities</strong></span></p><ul><li>Prepare cost and variations estimates, interim payment applications and payment certification for subcontracts, materials and plants</li><li>Carry out measurement for the purpose of subletting, material ordering, variation estimates and final accounts</li><li>Prepare contra-charge account against subcontractors</li><li>Assist in the implementation of the requirements of the Manuals in respect of all Quantity Surveying functions&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p><ul><li>Higher Diploma or Degree in Quantity Surveying or related disciplines</li><li>At least 4 years\' relevant experience</li><li>Experience in re-measurement, valuing variations, cost control, contract administration, claims preparation and dealing with sub-contractors\' accounts</li><li>Strong negotiation and communication skills</li><li>Fluent English and excellent writing skills</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr.p@buildking.hk\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">bkhr.p@buildking.hk</span></a><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">&nbsp;or clicking&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">Apply Online</span></a></p>'),(367,'Project Quantity Surveyor – Civil','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Responsibilities</strong></span></p><ul><li>Responsible for managing all aspects of project finance</li><li>Handle all post contract quantity surveying duties for the projects</li><li>Compile and update commercial accounts and records</li><li>Monitor the progress of related programmes</li><li>Provide recommendations on how to resolve issues with sub-contractors and suppliers</li><li>Assist in maintaining positive cash flow for the projects</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p><ul><li>Degree in Quantity Surveying or related disciplines</li><li>At least 7 years\' relevant experience</li><li>Experience in re-measurement, valuing variations, cost control, contract administration, claims preparation and dealing with sub-contractors\' accounts</li><li>MRICS or HKIS professional qualification will be added advantage</li><li>Strong negotiation and communication skills</li><li>Fluent English and excellent writing skills</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr.p@buildking.hk\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">bkhr.p@buildking.hk</span></a><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">&nbsp;or clicking&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">Apply Online</span></a></p>'),(368,'Business Analyst (Digital Projects) ','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Responsibilities</strong></span></p><ul><li>As the Business Analyst in the Digital Transformation Team, you will be involved with the latest Digital technology projects (e.g. ERP, GenAI, Cloud solution, IoT, Data Science, Mobile App, Digital platform, etc…)</li><li>Build and maintain strong relationships with both internal and external stakeholders throughout the project lifecycle to ensure a thorough understanding of requirements and their business impact</li><li>Conduct thorough analysis of existing digital processes and systems to identify areas for improvement and optimization</li><li>Create detailed requirements documentation that translates business needs into functional specifications for development teams</li><li>Convert business requirements into user stories</li><li>Conduct UAT with stakeholders and drive for sign off before feature release and make sure the developed features align with business requirements</li><li>Provide recommendations for ongoing feature enhancements</li><li>Working across different business and technology units</li><li>Assist the manager with daily operational and administrative tasks</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p><ul><li>Degree holder in Computer Science, Information Technology, Computer Engineering, Information Technology, or related disciplines</li><li>A minimum of 1-3 years of experience in IT Business Consultant or IT Project Management or ERP, or in a similar role</li><li>Sound knowledge of Agile or DevOps methodologies, including Scrum, is preferred</li><li>Problem-solving skill, multi-tasking skill, analytical skill, good communication and good time management</li><li>Self-motivated with excellent interpersonal, analytical skills, organization &amp; communication skills, shall be a good team player</li><li>Work independently, and good problem-solving skills</li><li>Technical/ Programming background would be an advantage</li><li>Certified Project Management Professional (PMP) or Prince2 or Scrum Master or DevOps would be an advantage</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr.c@buildking.hk\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">bkhr.c@buildking.hk</span></a><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">&nbsp;or clicking&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">Apply Online</span></a></p>'),(369,'Digital / Project Coordinator - Digital Technology Project ','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Responsibilities</strong></span></p><ul><li>As the Project Coordinator in the Digital Transformation Team, you will be involved with the latest Digital technology projects (e.g. ERP, GenAI, Cloud solution, IoT, Data Science, Mobile App, Digital platform, etc…)</li><li>Create detailed requirements documentation that translates business needs into functional specifications for development teams</li><li>Build and maintain strong relationships with both internal and external stakeholders throughout the project lifecycle to ensure a thorough understanding of requirements and their business impact</li><li>Develop comprehensive project documentation, including high-level and detailed requirement specifications, business process descriptions, and use cases for both major and minor projects</li><li>Working across different business and technology units</li><li>Assist the manager with daily operational and administrative tasks</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p><ul><li>Degree holder in Computer Science, Information Technology, Computer Engineering, Information Technology, or related disciplines</li><li>A minimum of 2-3 years of experience in IT Business Consultant or IT Project Management, or in a similar role</li><li>Digital knowledge: IoT, AI, Cloud (Azure, AWS, GCP), ERP (D365, SAP), Mobile App, Digital Twin, etc…</li><li>Sound knowledge of Agile or DevOps methodologies, including Scrum, is preferred</li><li>Problem-solving skill, multi-tasking skill, analytical skill, good communication and good time management</li><li>Self-motivated with excellent interpersonal, analytical skills, organization &amp; communication skills, shall be a good team player</li><li>Work independently, and good problem-solving skills</li><li>Technical/ Programming background would be an advantage</li><li>Certified Project Management Professional (PMP) or Prince2 or Scrum Master or DevOps would be an advantage</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr.c@buildking.hk\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">bkhr.c@buildking.hk</span></a><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">&nbsp;or clicking&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">Apply Online</span></a></p>'),(370,'Safety Officer - Civil / Building ','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Responsibilities</strong></span></p><ul><li>Ensure the Safety Regulations are complied with by maintaining frequent site inspections, training and liaison with site personnel, subcontractors and government official</li><li>Assist site management in monitoring the safety performance of workers and to provide safety advice to site management from time to time</li><li>Ensure, with the assistance of qualified first aid personnel that all first aid facilities are available for use in emergency and all equipment legally required are maintained in good working condition</li><li>Assist in accident investigation, if any; and recommending present measures to the site management</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p><ul><li>Registered Safety Officer with Labour Department</li><li>Bachelor Degree or Higher Diploma in&nbsp;Occupational Safety and Health or construction related subjects</li><li>Minimum 4 year\'s experience in construction field</li><li>Good command of spoken and written English &amp; Chinese</li><li>Hands on computer knowledge</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr.g@buildking.hk\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">bkhr.g@buildking.hk</span></a><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">&nbsp;or clicking&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">Apply Online</span></a></p>'),(371,'Assistant Safety Officer (Fresh Graduates are welcomed)','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Responsibilities</strong></span></p><ul><li>Support Supervisor to implement and maintain all safety systems and policies</li><li>Ensure the Safety Regulations are complied with by maintaining frequent site inspections, training and liaison with site personnel, subcontractors and government official</li><li>Monitor the subcontractor performance on occupational safety and health</li><li>Ensure, with the assistance of qualified first aid personnel that all first aid facilities are available for use in emergency and all equipment legally required are maintained in good working condition</li><li>Assist in accident investigation and recommending present measures to the site management</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p><ul><li>Bachelor Degree or Higher Diploma in&nbsp;Occupational Safety and Health or construction related subjects</li><li>1 year practical experience in construction preferably</li><li>Good command of spoken and written English &amp; Chinese</li><li>Hands on computer knowledge</li><li>Fresh Graduate will also be considered</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr.g@buildking.hk\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">bkhr.g@buildking.hk</span></a><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">&nbsp;or clicking&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">Apply Online</span></a></p>'),(372,'Labour Officer - Sheung Shui','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Responsibilities</strong></span></p><ul><li>Check and verify the proper operation of wages protection policies</li><li>Monitor the attendance, wage payments and MPF contributions to all site staff</li><li>Assist in handling and monitoring complaints on arrears of wages and MPF contributions raised by site staff</li><li>Ensure personal data and other personnel related matters as required of site staff / workers be submitted to Human Resources Department on time</li><li>Assist site administration duties when necessary</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p><ul><li>Form 5 / DSE graduate with full certificate</li><li>At least 1-2 years Labour Officer experience</li><li>Well-versed in Employment Ordinance and good PC knowledge</li><li>Mature and independent, with excellent communication and liaison skills</li><li>Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese</li><li>Immediate available is preferred</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr.g@buildking.hk\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">bkhr.g@buildking.hk</span></a><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">&nbsp;or clicking&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">Apply Online</span></a></p>'),(373,'Site Clerk ','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Responsibilities</strong></span></p><ul><li>Responsible for clerical / filing works,&nbsp;data entry and administrative works</li><li>Ability to handle project co-ordination and documentation</li><li>Assist in other ad hoc tasks as requested</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p><ul><li>F.5 / HKDSE or above with clerical / administrative / site&nbsp;experience</li><li>Able to work under pressure and meet deadline</li><li>Good typing skills (both Chinese and English) &amp; PC skills</li><li>Immediate available is highly preferred</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr.g@buildking.hk\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">bkhr.g@buildking.hk</span></a><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">&nbsp;or clicking&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">Apply Online</span></a></p>'),(374,'Surveying Assistant 測量助理 ','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">職責:</span></p><ul><li>負責於工地進行一般戶外平水測量及開線工作</li><li>收集測量數據</li><li>處理和保養測量儀器及工具</li><li>應上級指示執行測量工作</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">資歷要求:</span></p><ul><li>F.5 / HKDSE or above with clerical / administrative / site&nbsp;experience</li><li>Able to work under pressure and meet deadline</li><li>Good typing skills (both Chinese and English) &amp; PC skills</li><li>Immediate available is highly preferred</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><i>(受聘者有機會獲安排參加「承建商合作培訓計劃」(CCTS)&nbsp;或「中級技工合作培訓計劃」(ITCTS)&nbsp;或「強化建造業人力訓練計劃」 ( ECMTS)&nbsp; 接受培訓&nbsp;或&nbsp;「認可技術專才培訓計劃」(ATP))</i></span></p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\"><i>(The candidate may assign to participate in the&nbsp;\"Contractor Cooperation Training Program\" (CCTS)&nbsp;or&nbsp;\"Intermediate Tradesman Collaborative Training Scheme\" (ITCTS)&nbsp;for&nbsp;training or&nbsp;Approved Technical Talents Training Programmes (ATP))</i></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">員工福利：</span></p><ul><li>酌情性花紅</li><li>星期日及銀行假期休息</li><li>超時津貼</li><li>生日假</li><li>婚假</li><li>專業在職培訓</li><li>良好晉升機會</li><li>醫療福利</li><li>介紹人獎金</li><li>穿梭巴士-來往港鐵站</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr.g@buildking.hk\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">bkhr.g@buildking.hk</span></a><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">&nbsp;or clicking&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">Apply Online</span></a></p>'),(375,'Craft / Technician Apprentice - 工程學徒 (土木工程 / 樓宇建造 / 屋宇裝備 / 工料測量 / 工地測量 / 機械維修 / 冷氣設備)','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">有意參與基礎建設/土木工程/ 樓宇建造/ 屋宇裝備 / 工料測量 / 工地測量 / 機械維修 / 冷氣設備， 喜愛戶外工作， 具備合適數學根基，並有良好的理解及分析能力的人:</span></p><ul><li>透過完善學徒訓練計劃，學徒可在有系統、有規管及有支援的情況下累積工作經驗及繼續學業</li><li>獲公司資助，免費修讀文憑／高級文憑工程課程，並可於工作時間內上課</li><li>課程內容包括土木工程的理論、結構材料基本認識、建造工地測量及測量儀器之運用、建造工藝技術基本認識、基本合約文件、工程監督、建造工程相關法例及工程圖則等</li><li>完成整個學徒訓練可獲頒具廣泛認受的學徒畢業證書及擁有相關學歷和專業資格/牌照</li><li>參加「Earn and Learn 職學計劃」，首3年培訓期內可每月獲平均$3,000政府津貼</li><li>成功申請勞工處「展翅青見計劃」可報讀職外職業技能培訓課程及獲津貼資助</li><li>學徒事務署每年舉辦傑出學徒獎勵計劃，嘉許表現優異的註冊學徒。獲獎學徒有機會獲安排前往外地交流、考察和培訓</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">職責:</span></p><ul><li>工作範圍包括協助監督、管理、協調土木工程，如道路、水務、渠務、斜坡、地基、屋宇裝備等工程施工</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">資歷要求::</span></p><ul><li>中學文憑程度優先考慮；</li><li>好學勤奮，刻苦耐勞，具良好溝通技巧；及</li><li>有志投身建築行業，喜愛戶外工作，毋須工作經驗</li><li>工作地點: 東涌/ 屯門 / 元朗 / 大埔 / 葵芳 / 觀塘 / 油麻地/ 將軍澳 / 啟德</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr.ta@buildking.hk\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">bkhr.ta@buildking.hk</span></a><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">&nbsp;or clicking&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">Apply Online</span></a></p>'),(376,'地盤司機','<p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">職責:</span></p><ul><li>負責一般接送工作</li><li>執行公司指派的工作</li><li>保持車輛清潔及跟進維修保養事宜</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">要求:</span></p><ul><li>持有私家車駕駛執照</li><li>持有輕型貨車駕駛執照更佳</li><li>持有平安咭</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">待遇::</span></p><ul><li>星期一至六: 上午8時至下午6時</li><li>銀行假期</li><li>醫療保險</li><li>酌情性花紅</li><li>超時工作津貼</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human Resources Department&nbsp;by email:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" href=\"mailto:bkhr.g@buildking.hk\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">bkhr.g@buildking.hk</span></a><span style=\"color:#0099a7;\">&nbsp;or clicking&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\"> </span><a style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://forms.buildking.hk/bkh/form/JobApplication/formperma/ZGHQHcbl51ISP381z_DZzL1GgmMLGvGhMxkUVUJ5-V0\"><span style=\"color:hsl(0,0%,30%);\">Apply Online</span></a></p>'),(381,'Talent Development Programme','<figure class=\"table\" style=\"width:100%;\"><table class=\"ck-table-resized\" style=\"border-style:none;\"><colgroup><col style=\"width:65.24%;\"><col style=\"width:9.46%;\"><col style=\"width:25.3%;\"></colgroup><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:top;\"><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">The programme aims to develop a group of high-potential emerging management staff to become the Group’s future leaders. The selected staff are guided and coached by responsible directors according to personalised career and development plans tailored to their growth ambitions and professional goals.</p></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"large_tdp_69e70bdfb8.jpeg\" src=\"http://20.255.252.230/uploads/large_tdp_69e70bdfb8_751971f2db.jpeg\" srcset=\"http://20.255.252.230/uploads/thumbnail_large_tdp_69e70bdfb8_751971f2db.jpeg 208w, http://20.255.252.230/uploads/small_large_tdp_69e70bdfb8_751971f2db.jpeg 500w, http://20.255.252.230/uploads/medium_large_tdp_69e70bdfb8_751971f2db.jpeg 750w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"750\"></figure></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>'),(382,'Graduate Engineer Programme (Scheme “A” Training)','<figure class=\"table\" style=\"width:100%;\"><table class=\"ck-table-resized\" style=\"border-style:none;\"><colgroup><col style=\"width:65.24%;\"><col style=\"width:9.46%;\"><col style=\"width:25.3%;\"></colgroup><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:top;\"><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">The programme has been registered with Hong Kong Institute of Engineers since 1996. Our approved disciplines include Civil, Building and Building Services. We have trained over hundreds of professionally qualified engineers, many of them are holding key management positions in the Group.</p></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"large_grad_e_prog_2647cd8b80.jpeg\" src=\"http://20.255.252.230/uploads/large_grad_e_prog_2647cd8b80_1b2de2245e.jpeg\" srcset=\"http://20.255.252.230/uploads/thumbnail_large_grad_e_prog_2647cd8b80_1b2de2245e.jpeg 208w, http://20.255.252.230/uploads/small_large_grad_e_prog_2647cd8b80_1b2de2245e.jpeg 500w, http://20.255.252.230/uploads/medium_large_grad_e_prog_2647cd8b80_1b2de2245e.jpeg 750w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"750\"></figure><figure class=\"image\"><img></figure></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>'),(383,'Graduate Land Surveyor Programme','<figure class=\"table\" style=\"width:100%;\"><table class=\"ck-table-resized\" style=\"border-style:none;\"><colgroup><col style=\"width:65.24%;\"><col style=\"width:9.46%;\"><col style=\"width:25.3%;\"></colgroup><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:top;\"><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">The programme is well structured and carefully designed so that it provides comprehensive learning opportunities for GLSs to acquire technical knowledge, site experience and management techniques in a way that fulfills the requirement of Corporate Members of the Hong Kong Institute of Surveyors/ Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors.</p></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"large_grad_landsurveyor_prog_8175052a8f.jpeg\" src=\"http://20.255.252.230/uploads/large_grad_landsurveyor_prog_8175052a8f_5db1161a3b.jpeg\" srcset=\"http://20.255.252.230/uploads/thumbnail_large_grad_landsurveyor_prog_8175052a8f_5db1161a3b.jpeg 208w, http://20.255.252.230/uploads/small_large_grad_landsurveyor_prog_8175052a8f_5db1161a3b.jpeg 500w, http://20.255.252.230/uploads/medium_large_grad_landsurveyor_prog_8175052a8f_5db1161a3b.jpeg 750w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"750\"></figure></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>'),(384,'Quantity Surveying Programme','<figure class=\"table\" style=\"width:100%;\"><table class=\"ck-table-resized\" style=\"border-style:none;\"><colgroup><col style=\"width:65.24%;\"><col style=\"width:9.46%;\"><col style=\"width:25.3%;\"></colgroup><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:top;\"><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Our Assistant Quantity Surveyors are encouraged to join this three-years programme in which intensive on-job training, project rotations and professional training are provided. Mock interviews and presentations practice are also offered to support trainees to successfully complete professional assessments of Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors/Hong Kong Institute of Surveyors.</p></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"large_qs_prog_65da13c597.jpeg\" src=\"http://20.255.252.230/uploads/large_qs_prog_65da13c597_2f082fd1e0.jpeg\" srcset=\"http://20.255.252.230/uploads/thumbnail_large_qs_prog_65da13c597_2f082fd1e0.jpeg 208w, http://20.255.252.230/uploads/small_large_qs_prog_65da13c597_2f082fd1e0.jpeg 500w, http://20.255.252.230/uploads/medium_large_qs_prog_65da13c597_2f082fd1e0.jpeg 750w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"750\"></figure></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>'),(385,'Apprenticeship Programme','<figure class=\"table\" style=\"width:100%;\"><table class=\"ck-table-resized\" style=\"border-style:none;\"><colgroup><col style=\"width:65.24%;\"><col style=\"width:9.46%;\"><col style=\"width:25.3%;\"></colgroup><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:top;\